browser-cache-clearer

A Node.js utility for clearing browser cache folders (Chrome and Edge) from the filesystem on macOS and Windows.
It deletes local cache files and directories to help reclaim space or reset browser states.


Installation

npm install browser-cache-clearer

Usage

import { clear } from 'browser-cache-clearer';

console.log('üßº Starting browser cache cleanup...');

try {

  clear();

  console.log('‚úÖ Cache cleanup completed for Chrome and Edge.');
} catch (error) {

  console.error('‚ùå Failed to clear browser cache:', error.message);
}


‚ö†Ô∏è Limitations

‚ùå Does NOT work in:

Browsers (like React apps in the browser) ‚Äì This package uses fs, path, and os Node modules which are not available in browser environments.

Linux ‚Äì Not yet supported.

Electron apps ‚Äì Unless configured with proper Node integration.


‚úÖ Works in:

Node.js CLI scripts

Backend Node.js services

Desktop apps built with Node.js + system access


üìÅ What It Deletes
Chrome/Edge cache folders like:

Cache

GPUCache

Code Cache

Service Worker/CacheStorage

Application Cache

For both Default profile users in the following locations:

macOS:
~/Library/Caches/Google/Chrome/Default/...

~/Library/Caches/Microsoft Edge/Default/...

Windows:
C:\Users\YOUR_NAME\AppData\Local\Google\Chrome\User Data\Default\...

C:\Users\YOUR_NAME\AppData\Local\Microsoft\Edge\User Data\Default\...

